body:
Blueprint of typical tasks:
	Collecting and first processing of incoming support requests (Incidents);
	Taking first action to solve addressed problems;
	Providing a detailed error message permitting a reproduction of any reported error in testing and support environment;
	Developing standard user manuals, installation and support documents;
	Providing support for installation of PCs, peripheral devices, software;
	Active involvement in projects / assistance for project manager; communicate and interact with consultants and other project members;
	Incident management and reporting through ticketing system (SysAid);
	Participating in “train the trainer” sessions in order to acquire skills and knowledge for supported system;
	Active participation in end users training sessions and end users’ assistance in post implementation period
	Providing support in the execution of plans for change management activities. 

Position requirements
	BS Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or related field
	At least one-year experience as a Software Support Engineer or similar 
	Experience / Knowledge of Incident tracking systems, help desk environment
	Incident process understanding (ITIL foundation is a plus)
	Sound knowledge of Software Development Life Cycle methodologies / Project Management processes
	Advanced knowledge of Microsoft® Office products (Windows® Word, Excel and Outlook)
	Very good written and spoken English skills
	Availability for travelling to implementation sites 
	Good understanding of hardware devices
	Willingness to keep him/herself abreast with the latest developments in his/her area of expertise
